<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - PREVENTIVE MAINTENANCE -
        MASTER CLUTCH SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MASTER CLUTCH SYSTEM</title>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Lubricate clutch release pedal shaft bushings at every chassis lubrication interval. There should
                    be one grease fitting on each side of the transmission clutch housing.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Have the clutch checked and adjusted if any of the following occurs:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Clutch does not disengage completely.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Clutch brake does not function.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Clutch pedal free play is less than 1/2 inch.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>When replacing the clutch, use a high quality spring damped replacement unit.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
